── Suggested Actions ────────────────────

{% if alert_type == "pi_offline" %}
• Check Raspberry Pi power supply and network cable
• Verify Mosquitto broker is running: sudo systemctl status mosquitto
• Check Pi drive controller: sudo systemctl status oak-drive-controller
• Try SSH: ssh pi@{{ pi_ip | default("192.168.1.100") }}
{% elif alert_type == "camera_offline" %}
• Check PoE++ switch port LEDs for the affected camera
• Verify camera power draw is within PoE budget
• Restart DepthAI pipeline on the Windows controller
• Try: python -c "import depthai; print(depthai.Device.getAllAvailableDevices())"
{% elif alert_type == "broker_offline" %}
• The MQTT broker on the Pi may have crashed
• SSH into Pi and check: sudo systemctl status mosquitto
• Restart if needed: sudo systemctl restart mosquitto
• Check logs: sudo tail -50 /var/log/mosquitto/mosquitto.log
{% elif alert_type == "drive_fault" %}
• A mechanical drive has reported a fault (stall or limit switch)
• Inspect the physical drive mechanism for obstructions
• Check wiring between Pi GPIO and motor driver
• After fixing, send a home command to recalibrate
{% elif alert_type == "sequence_aborted" %}
• The capture sequence was stopped due to repeated errors
• Check the error log for the root cause
• Resolve the underlying issue, then restart the sequence
{% else %}
• Check system logs for details
• Verify all network connections are stable
• Restart affected components if necessary
{% endif %}

